WEBVTT

00:06.520 --> 00:07.509
Almost there.

00:09.400 --> 00:12.437
All the way from the parking lot.
I told you I could do it!

00:12.520 --> 00:14.556
Who's the idiot now?

00:16.200 --> 00:19.636
<i>Despite my burning thighs, giving</i>
<i>that piggyback ride was worth it,</i>

00:19.720 --> 00:21.836
<i>because I'm sure it put him</i>
<i>in a great mood.</i>

00:21.920 --> 00:24.309
- I'm in a worse mood.
- <i>Why did I do it?</i>

00:24.400 --> 00:26.550
Kelso's got this stupid outreach program

00:26.640 --> 00:29.154
where families are allowed
to observe surgeries.

00:29.240 --> 00:31.708
Yesterday, I had to do
a bypass on this guy.

00:32.080 --> 00:34.071
You should have seen that family...

00:34.720 --> 00:38.554
Standing there emotionless.
Silently judging me.

00:38.640 --> 00:41.871
And today I gotta do
a colectomy on that guy.

00:42.800 --> 00:45.678
What do you think
his family's gonna be like?

00:46.680 --> 00:48.079
There's a tumour in there!

00:48.160 --> 00:51.470
- There's a tumour in there!
- Don't go behind the kidney, brother!

00:55.520 --> 00:57.317
You didn't go to the black family

00:57.400 --> 00:59.868
yelling at the movie screen
stereotype, did you?

00:59.960 --> 01:01.473
Like a bear to honey.

01:01.560 --> 01:03.915
I was supposed to
be downstairs ten minutes ago

01:04.000 --> 01:07.117
to talk to pre-med students
about what it's like to be a doctor.

01:07.200 --> 01:08.918
Don't worry. I gotcha.

01:11.440 --> 01:13.351
Buckle up, buddy.

01:19.240 --> 01:20.593
Hell, yeah!

01:20.680 --> 01:22.193
Hey, kids, I'm Dr Dorian.

01:22.280 --> 01:25.272
I'm sure you have lots of questions,
so let's get started.

01:25.680 --> 01:27.796
So basically, it's a topical application

01:27.880 --> 01:31.350
consisting of equal parts
triethanolamine and phenyl dimethicone.

01:31.440 --> 01:34.352
I suggest applying it
twice a day for extra hold, OK?

01:34.440 --> 01:36.670
Here's a sample tube, Reuben.

01:36.760 --> 01:40.548
Excellent query.
OK, then. Anybody else?

01:41.160 --> 01:42.673
Reuben again.

01:42.760 --> 01:46.150
What was your best moment in medicine?

01:46.240 --> 01:50.199
I'd say my best moment was probably
my second year, New Year's eve.

01:50.280 --> 01:53.556
A young pregnant woman
could barely make it to the hospital.

01:53.640 --> 01:56.791
She had her baby
right there on the ramp.

02:01.560 --> 02:03.551
You know, that's my first grandchild.

02:03.640 --> 02:05.153
Did you deliver him?

02:05.240 --> 02:07.117
No, I didn't. But I did watch.

02:07.200 --> 02:09.316
And I am a doctor.

02:09.400 --> 02:11.709
And you look amazing!

02:11.800 --> 02:14.758
So even though Dr Mickhead
actually delivered the kid,

02:14.840 --> 02:18.355
yours truly rang in
the new year with grandma.

02:20.120 --> 02:21.838
We had sex.

02:23.400 --> 02:25.516
That's how I do it.

02:25.600 --> 02:27.636
That was your best moment?

02:27.720 --> 02:28.994
I totally get it.

02:29.080 --> 02:30.752
Older ladies know how to work it.

02:30.840 --> 02:34.515
OK. Now you're in a bit of a pickle,
cos the older lady you're talking about

02:34.600 --> 02:37.717
better not be me and it sure
as hell better not be somebody else.

02:37.800 --> 02:41.759
- So, what do you have to say?
- Your favourite jeans are too tight.

02:41.840 --> 02:43.831
- They look ridiculous.
- What?!

02:43.920 --> 02:46.275
I'm in trouble anyway,
and it needed to be said.

02:46.360 --> 02:48.954
Unfortunately for you,
that's not true. Right?

02:51.920 --> 02:52.989
Wow.

02:53.080 --> 02:56.072
I'll tell you what my
best moment in medicine was.

02:57.360 --> 02:59.351
Damn! We lost him.

02:59.440 --> 03:02.477
- Call it.
- I'm not giving up on this guy.

03:02.560 --> 03:04.312
- Prop his hand up.
- What?

03:04.400 --> 03:06.436
I said prop his hand up!

03:14.720 --> 03:17.188
That's right. The miracle five.

03:17.280 --> 03:19.874
- You take this one, Perry.
- Great moment, dumb ass.

03:19.960 --> 03:23.430
Starts with a profound misunderstanding
of how the human body works,

03:23.520 --> 03:26.159
and winds up with you
shattering some old man's hand.

03:26.240 --> 03:27.514
Oh, yeah.

03:27.600 --> 03:29.591
Know what'd be neat?
If you took a second

03:29.680 --> 03:32.478
and thought about what your
best moment in medicine was.

03:39.040 --> 03:41.031
It would have been neat.

